The paper focuses on traffic engineering in software defined networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the need for quick reaction to failures and utilization of priority queues, which are topics related to system design and control (cs.SY). The paper proposes a new TE system that can handle heavily-loaded networks, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the optimization of maximizing overall throughput, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the need to handle bursty traffic spikes, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR).
